=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: From 1-bromo-2-iodo-4-nitrobenzene, do a chemoselective Suzuki coupling at the iodide with cyclohex-1-en-1-yl boronic acid (or Bpin) to give 1-bromo-2-(cyclohex-1-en-1-yl)-4-nitrobenzene. | Step 2: Convert the aryl bromide to the aryllithium/Grignard and add to methyl tetrahydropyran-4-one-4-carboxylate to form methyl 4-[2-(cyclohex-1-en-1-yl)-4-nitrophenyl]-4-hydroxytetrahydro-2H-pyran-4-carboxylate. | Step 3: Reductively deoxygenate the tertiary alcohol (e.g. Et3SiH/BF3·OEt2) to give methyl 4-[2-(cyclohex-1-en-1-yl)-4-nitrophenyl]tetrahydro-2H-pyran-4-carboxylate. | Step 4: Reduce the nitro group (H2/Pd-C, Fe/HCl, or SnCl2) to obtain methyl 4-[4-amino-2-(cyclohex-1-en-1-yl)phenyl]tetrahydro-2H-pyran-4-carboxylate. | Step 5: In parallel, prepare 2-cyano-6-(2-trimethylsilylethoxymethyl)pyrimidine-4-carboxylic acid from a suitable cyanopyrimidine ester precursor by installing the CH2OCH2CH2SiMe3 substituent via chloromethyl substitution/alkoxymethylation, then hydrolyzing the ester to the acid; optionally convert to the acid chloride. | Step 6: Couple the aniline from Step 4 with the pyrimidine-4-carboxylic acid derivative from Step 5 (acid chloride or HATU/EDC coupling) to furnish the target COC(=O)C1(c2ccc(NC(=O)c3nc(C#N)cn3COCC[Si](C)(C)C)c(C3=CCCCC3)c2)CCOCC1.

